# `git archive` produces a release tarball without the dev-only paths
# below — useful for users who want to install the skill from a release
# artifact rather than via the Claude Code marketplace. Has no effect on
# `git clone`, `/plugin install`, or the working tree; only the archive.
#
# Runtime needs: SKILL.md, scripts/, prompts/, references/, package.json,
# pnpm-lock.yaml, action.yml, .claude-plugin/. Everything else is either
# diploma scaffolding (benchmark/, docs/, examples/) or dev tooling
# (eslint, vitest, ci/, .github/).

benchmark/        export-ignore
docs/             export-ignore
examples/         export-ignore
coverage/         export-ignore
ci/               export-ignore
.github/          export-ignore
.editorconfig     export-ignore
.eslintrc*        export-ignore
.node-version     export-ignore
.nvmrc            export-ignore
.npmrc            export-ignore
.pre-commit-hooks.yaml  export-ignore
eslint.config.mjs export-ignore
vitest.config.mjs export-ignore
CHANGELOG.md      export-ignore
CONTRIBUTING.md   export-ignore
